pros:
Amazon is a very healthy, growing company and if one wants to work in the Amazon Web Services division it is growing very rapidly and is a good resume experience-builder for younger developers.

Overall, I have had excellent cooperation from management in having a flexible schedule and support in managing difficult family matters;

While not as cutting-edge as Google in many respects, Amazon does tend to make use of recent technologies and moves along technically at a fair clip in most areas.

cons:
fast paced environment; the pressure to perform, and always perform is across the company hierarchy; 
 
little work-life balance unless you are very lucky to get a compassionate boss;

Time-off benefits, like maternity leave or holidays, are nothing more than just meeting laws.
